Comment: You're right, ScienceDuck, it's rather extraordinary  seeing a couple  of folks who famously preserve their own anonymity using this forum  to spread personal attacks about another  commenter. Especially when they are using false info.
Fortunately I have nothing  to hide-- the check from the MEF demonstrated that Pipes' charges were false;
And for anyone who is familiar with student evaluations, those 12 non-random posts  on a commercial site ranging from Awful to Awesome mean nothing relative  to my many years of good evaluations received by the Soc Department.  
What they do reflect, as a group, is that: The courses I taught covered subjects as emotional and politically charged as those fought over on this forum--giving everyone  with wildly different views a chance to speak while still keeping order was a challenge;
 and at 70, I was most definitely not a "hottie!"
